courses.course_description: Introduces relational database management systems as a class of software systems. Architectural foundations, design issues, and implementation techniques are covered.
Presents the mathematical techniques used for the design and analysis of computer algorithms. Focuses on algorithmic design paradigms and techniques for analyzing the correctness and running time.
Introduces core concepts and methods in artificial intelligence including search strategies, knowledge representation, reasoning, machine learning fundamentals.
Studies the structure, components, and operation of computer systems. Topics include computer architecture, operating systems, and systems programming.
Network protocols, architecture, routing algorithms, congestion control, wireless networks, and network security.
Security threats, cryptography, network security, web security, malware analysis, and security best practices.
3D graphics pipeline, transformations, lighting, shading, texture mapping, ray tracing, and GPU programming.
Principles of distributed computing, consensus algorithms, replication, fault tolerance, and cloud computing.
Software development methodologies, requirements engineering, design patterns, testing, project management, and agile methods.
Theory and application of discrete-time signals and systems, frequency domain analysis, filter design, sampling theorem, and digital signal processing applications.
Analysis of electric power systems including power flow, fault analysis, stability, and modern grid technologies.
Linear control theory, state-space methods, stability analysis, controller design, and digital control systems.
Digital modulation, error control coding, channel capacity, wireless communication systems, and modern communication standards.
Design of integrated circuits, CMOS technology, circuit simulation, layout, timing analysis, and chip testing.
Vector spaces, linear transformations, matrices, systems of linear equations, eigenvalues, and applications to engineering and science.
Rigorous treatment of limits, continuity, differentiation, integration, sequences and series of functions, metric spaces.
Computational methods for solving mathematical problems, error analysis, interpolation, numerical integration, differential equations.
Linear and nonlinear optimization, convex optimization, dynamic programming, and applications in engineering and science.
Ordinary and partial differential equations, existence and uniqueness theorems, numerical solutions, and applications.
Introduction to quantum physics including wave functions, Schrodinger equation, quantum states, measurement theory, and applications.
Advanced classical mechanics including Lagrangian and Hamiltonian formulations, rigid body dynamics, and nonlinear dynamics.
Statistical description of physical systems, ensemble theory, quantum statistics, phase transitions, and applications.
Crystal structure, electronic properties of solids, semiconductors, superconductivity, and magnetic materials.
Numerical methods in physics, Monte Carlo simulations, molecular dynamics, finite element methods, and parallel computing.
Structure and function of cells, cellular organelles, cell signaling, cell cycle, and molecular mechanisms of cellular processes.
Modern genetics including molecular genetics, genomics, population genetics, and computational approaches to genetic analysis.
Gene expression, DNA replication, transcription, translation, gene regulation, and molecular biology techniques.
Structure and function of the nervous system, neural signaling, sensory systems, motor control, and cognitive neuroscience.
Structure, properties, and reactions of organic compounds. Mechanisms of organic reactions and synthetic strategies.
Thermodynamics, kinetics, quantum chemistry, and spectroscopy. Mathematical treatment of chemical phenomena.
Modern analytical techniques including spectroscopy, chromatography, mass spectrometry, and electrochemical methods.
Structure and function of proteins, enzymes, metabolism, bioenergetics, and regulation of biochemical pathways.
Fundamentals of data science including data manipulation, visualization, statistical analysis, and basic machine learning using Python.
Supervised and unsupervised learning algorithms, neural networks, deep learning, model evaluation, and practical applications.
Neural network architectures, convolutional networks, recurrent networks, transformers, and applications in computer vision and NLP.
Text processing, language models, sentiment analysis, machine translation, and modern NLP architectures.
Distributed data processing, Hadoop, Spark, NoSQL databases, stream processing, and scalable analytics.
Laws of thermodynamics, entropy, energy conversion, power cycles, refrigeration, and applications to engineering systems.
Fluid statics and dynamics, conservation laws, dimensional analysis, flow in pipes, boundary layers, and computational fluid dynamics.
Robot kinematics, dynamics, control, path planning, sensors, and artificial intelligence in robotics.
Structure and properties of materials, phase diagrams, mechanical properties, failure analysis, and material selection.
Probability theory, random variables, sampling distributions, estimation, hypothesis testing, and confidence intervals.
Statistical methods for analyzing time-dependent data, ARIMA models, forecasting, spectral analysis.
Bayesian inference, prior distributions, MCMC methods, hierarchical models, and Bayesian computation.
Design and analysis of experiments, ANOVA, factorial designs, response surface methods, and applications.
Design and application of electronic instrumentation for biological measurements, sensors, signal conditioning, and medical devices.
Materials used in medical devices and implants, biocompatibility, tissue engineering, drug delivery systems.
Principles of medical imaging modalities including X-ray, CT, MRI, ultrasound, image processing and reconstruction.
Software design principles, development methodologies, version control, testing strategies, and team collaboration.
Biochemical processes, protein structure and function, enzyme kinetics, metabolic pathways, and molecular biology techniques.
Ecological principles, population dynamics, community ecology, evolutionary theory, and conservation biology.
Structure and bonding in inorganic compounds, coordination chemistry, organometallic chemistry, and solid-state chemistry.
Chemical processes in the environment, atmospheric chemistry, water chemistry, pollution, and environmental analysis.

courses.course_name: Data Structures and Algorithms for Data Science
courses.course_description: Fundamental data structures, algorithm analysis, optimization techniques, and their applications in data science.
Principles of visual design, interactive visualizations, dashboard creation, and storytelling with data.
Microcontroller programming, real-time systems, hardware-software integration, and IoT applications.
Groups, rings, fields, Galois theory, and applications to cryptography and coding theory.
Kinematics and kinetics of particles and rigid bodies, vibration analysis, modal analysis, and dynamic system modeling.
Conduction, convection, radiation, heat exchangers, and computational heat transfer methods.
Linear regression, ANOVA, generalized linear models, mixed models, and applications in data analysis.
Multivariate distributions, principal component analysis, factor analysis, discriminant analysis, and clustering.
Principles of tissue engineering, scaffold design, cell culture, bioreactors, and regenerative medicine applications.
Mechanics of biological tissues, musculoskeletal biomechanics, cardiovascular mechanics, and computational modeling.
